createVault(address,address,uint24,uint1.details: tokenA and tokenB may be passed in either order: token0/token1 or token1/token0. The call will revert if the vault already exists, the fee is invalid, or the token arguments are invalid.

params._fee: The desired fee for the unipilot vault
params._tokenA: The first token of the pool by address sort order
params._tokenB: The second token of the pool by address sort order

returns._vault: The address of the newly created pool

returns._0: governance address, strategy address, indexFund address

setGovernance(address).details: Must be called by the current governance

params._newGovernance: The new governance of the Unipilot factory

setUnipilotDetails(address,address,uint8.details: Must be called by the current governance

params._indexFundPercentage: Percentage of fees for index fund

createVault(address,address,uint24,uint1.notice: Creates a vault for the given two tokens and fee

getUnipilotDetails().notice: Used to give addresses of governance, strategy, indexFund

setGovernance(address).notice: Updates the governance of the Unipilot factory

setUnipilotDetails(address,address,uint8.notice: Updates all the necessary Unipilot details used in active vaults
